        "### Overall Findings\n",
        "\n",
        "Exploratory data analysis indicates that credit approval outcomes are driven primarily by indicators of **financial stability and credit reliability**, particularly:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Prior default history  \n",
        "- Credit score  \n",
        "- Employment status and tenure  \n",
        "- Existing banking relationship  \n",
        "\n",
        "Demographic variables showed some variation in financial characteristics but largely appear to act as **indirect contextual factors rather than primary predictors**. The goal moving forward is to prepare the dataset for modeling while preserving interpretability, minimizing redundancy, and avoiding unnecessary feature complexity.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Variables to Retain Without Major Adjustment\n",
        "\n",
        "These variables demonstrated strong, consistent relationships with approval outcomes and can be retained largely as-is.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Core Financial Predictors\n",
        "\n",
        "**PriorDefault**\n",
        "- Strongest predictor of approval outcomes.\n",
        "- Direct indicator of repayment risk.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Employed**\n",
        "- Reflects income stability.\n",
        "- Moderately strong relationship with approval outcomes.\n",
        "\n",
        "**YearsEmployed**\n",
        "- Captures employment stability beyond simple employment status.\n",
        "- Provides interpretable insight into financial reliability.\n",
        "\n",
        "**BankCustomer**\n",
        "- Indicates an existing financial relationship with the institution.\n",
        "- Likely reflects prior financial trust and information availability.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Supporting Context Variables\n",
        "\n",
        "**Debt**\n",
        "- Moderately predictive.\n",
        "- Most meaningful when interpreted alongside income and credit score.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Industry**\n",
        "- Provides employment-sector context.\n",
        "- May indirectly reflect income stability or job security.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Ethnicity**\n",
        "- Shows variation in financial indicators such as credit score and employment tenure.\n",
        "- Retained cautiously for contextual interpretation rather than direct prediction.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Variables Requiring Adjustment Before Modeling\n",
        "\n",
        "These variables contain useful information but benefit from limited preprocessing to ensure reliability while maintaining interpretability.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Credit Score (Scaled Variable — Tree-Based Categorization Applied)\n",
        "\n",
        "Credit score appeared scaled in the dataset but demonstrated strong predictive power. To address scaling ambiguity while preserving interpretability, a **decision-tree-based binning approach** was used to create categorical credit score groupings based on approval outcomes.\n",
        "\n",
        "This transformation has already been applied.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Rationale:**\n",
        "- Data-driven grouping preserves predictive structure.\n",
        "- Avoids arbitrary thresholds.\n",
        "- Improves interpretability through discrete risk categories.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Income (Skewed Distribution)\n",
        "\n",
        "Income shows substantial skewness and extreme outliers.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Recommended Adjustment:**\n",
        "- Apply log transformation or robust scaling.\n",
        "- Avoid aggressive binning to preserve interpretability.\n",
        "- Consider mild outlier capping if extreme values distort modeling.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Zip Code (Geographic Context Variable)\n",
        "\n",
        "Zip code behaves categorically rather than numerically.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Recommended Adjustment:**\n",
        "- Treat as categorical.\n",
        "- Group into broader geographic clusters if needed.\n",
        "- Avoid high-dimensional one-hot encoding given dataset size.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Debt (Outlier Sensitivity)\n",
        "\n",
        "Debt values show variability and some extreme observations.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Recommended Adjustment:**\n",
        "- Monitor for outlier influence.\n",
        "- Interpret alongside income and credit score.\n",
        "- Avoid heavy transformation unless modeling instability appears.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Variables Recommended for Removal\n",
        "\n",
        "These variables were removed due to weak predictive signal, redundancy, or reliability concerns identified during EDA.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Age\n",
        "- Minimal separation between approval groups.\n",
        "- Moderately correlated with years employed.\n",
        "- Limited additional predictive value.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Conclusion:** Removed to reduce redundancy and simplify interpretation.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Marital Status\n",
        "- Extremely strong correlation with bank customer status.\n",
        "- Likely redundant financial relationship indicator.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Conclusion:** Removed due to multicollinearity.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Citizenship Status\n",
        "- Severe class imbalance, particularly among temporary citizens.\n",
        "- Small subgroup sizes reduce reliability.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Conclusion:** Removed due to imbalance and interpretability concerns.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Gender\n",
        "- Minimal independent predictive signal.\n",
        "- Potential regulatory and fairness sensitivity.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Conclusion:** Removed to simplify modeling.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Driver’s License\n",
        "- Weak relationship with approval outcomes.\n",
        "- Likely administrative rather than financial indicator.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Conclusion:** Removed due to low predictive relevance.\n",
