      "source": [
        "**Info on decision-tree-based binning**: chooses split points with highest info gain to find non-linear thresholds and more solidified cutoff values"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FOdPou_uOWox"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Determine bins for credit score using decision-tree–based information-theoretic binning\n",
        "X = crd_dta[[\"CreditScore\"]]\n",
        "y = crd_dta[\"Approved\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "# initialize the tree\n",
        "tree = DecisionTreeClassifier(\n",
        "    criterion=\"entropy\",      # information gain\n",
        "    max_leaf_nodes=5,         # number of bins\n",
        "    min_samples_leaf=0.10,    # at least 10% of data per bin\n",
        "    random_state=42\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# fit it on the data\n",
        "tree.fit(X, y)"
      ],
