        "```\n",
        "| Model                     | Optimal Threshold (CV) | Optimal Fβ (CV) | beta | Test Accuracy | Test Precision | Test Recall | Test F1 | Test Fβ | Test ROC-AUC |\n",
        "| ------------------------- | ---------------------- | --------------- | ---- | ------------- | -------------- | ----------- | ------- | ------- | ------------ |\n",
        "| Lasso Logistic Regression | 0.38                   | 0.892           | 2.0  | 0.861         | 0.848          | 0.881       | 0.864   | 0.874   | 0.927        |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Logic Behind the Function**\n",
        "\n",
        "This function follows a *leakage-safe* workflow for selecting a classification threshold and then evaluating performance:\n",
        "\n",
        "1) **Cross-Validation Threshold Tuning (Training Data Only)**  \n",
        "   - The training set is split using `StratifiedKFold` to preserve class balance in each fold.  \n",
        "   - For each fold, the model is fit on the fold’s training portion and used to generate **out-of-fold (OOF) scores** (probabilities or decision scores) for the fold’s validation portion.  \n",
        "   - Once every training row has an OOF score, the function searches over candidate thresholds and chooses the threshold that **maximizes Fβ** on the OOF predictions.\n",
        "\n",
        "   *Why Fβ?*  \n",
        "   - Fβ lets you control the precision/recall tradeoff:\n",
        "     - **β = 1** → F1 (balanced)\n",
        "     - **β > 1** → prioritizes recall (capture more likely approvals)\n",
        "     - **β < 1** → prioritizes precision (avoid wasted promotions)\n",
        "\n",
        "2) **Final Model Fit (Full Training Set)**  \n",
        "   - After selecting the best threshold, the model is retrained once on the full training set.\n",
        "\n",
        "3) **Test Evaluation (Fixed Threshold)**  \n",
        "   - The selected threshold is applied to the **test-set scores** to produce binary predictions.  \n",
        "   - Test metrics are then computed using that fixed threshold: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1, and **Test Fβ**.  \n",
        "   - **ROC-AUC** is computed from the continuous test scores and is threshold-independent.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why this avoids leakage**  \n",
        "- The threshold is tuned using only training data (via OOF predictions), and the test set is used only once at the end for unbiased evaluation."
      ],
