    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "*Findings*:\n",
        "  - Naive Bayes created an extremely small Optimal threshold, meaning that the predicted probabilites for the positive class were extremely small so to compinsate it lowered the threshold extremely. This means that the model is poorly calibrated compared to logistic regression\n",
        "  - It is struggling to correctly identify the negatives\n",
        "  - The reason behind this underperformance is Naive Bayes assumes that the features are conditionally independent from each other, but we have correlations between the variables (ex: income with credit score), which violates this assumption and distorts probabilites"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "o4ekdt1CU5uC"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Tree based models\n",
        "To capture nonlinear relationships and interaction effects automatically:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Decision Tree (interpretable nonlinear baseline)\n",
        "- Random Forest (ensemble averaging to reduce variance)\n",
        "- XGBoost (gradient boosting for improved predictive performance)\n",
        "\n",
        "These models allow comparison between simple interpretable trees and more advanced ensemble methods."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "k_OOysgTU-m8"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Decision Tree**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ens281f3VAoa"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# create a decision tree pipeline\n",
        "dtree_pipe = Pipeline([\n",
        "    (\"model\", DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42))\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# create a parameter grid to grid search\n",
        "param_grid = {\n",
        "    \"model__max_depth\": [3, 5, 8, None],\n",
        "    \"model__min_samples_split\": [2, 10, 25],\n",
        "    \"model__min_samples_leaf\": [1, 5, 10],\n",
        "    \"model__ccp_alpha\": [0.0, 0.001, 0.01]  # pruning strength\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "# Grid search optimize on roc_auc (so we can tune the threshold based on FB later)\n",
        "grid_dt = GridSearchCV(\n",
        "    estimator=dtree_pipe,\n",
        "    param_grid=param_grid,\n",
        "    scoring=\"roc_auc\",\n",
        "    cv=5,\n",
        "    n_jobs=-1\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "grid_dt.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "best_dtree = grid_dt.best_estimator_\n",
        "print(\"Best params:\", grid_dt.best_params_)\n",
        "print(\"Best CV ROC-AUC:\", grid_dt.best_score_)"
      ],
