    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "*Findings*:\n",
        "\n",
        "  - The decision tree ran into a similar issue as the Naive Bayes model, due to the leafs likely having few samples or imbalances. Since it is a single tree the model is prone to noise (which is common in a credit card approval dataset), thus it likely has underconfident assignments to the test data.\n",
        "  - Additionally the objective B=2 optimizes recall heavier than precision, thus it tries to capture as many true approvals as it cans. In order to do this the model lowers the threshold quite heavily to compinsate for the uncertain predictions\n",
        "  - In a single sentence: Because of high correlation with dependent vars and noise in credit card data the results are likely to be more confident with a linear model"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-a18A26ZVL5N"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Random Forest**:\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Expectation: should reduce variance and result in more stable probability estimates, while also handling the correlation between variables much better. The hope is that this will find non-linear patterns that logistic regression could not find while not failing due to similar issues decision tree ran into"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Swg-7HvtVPUc"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# create params dictionary to test\n",
        "param_dist = {\n",
        "    \"model__n_estimators\": [300, 500, 800], # number of trees in the forest\n",
        "    \"model__max_depth\": [None, 5, 10, 20], # controlling complexity of trees (with no cutoff we could overfit with a fully grown tree)\n",
        "    \"model__min_samples_split\": [2, 10, 25], # minimum samples in each split (cutoff)\n",
        "    \"model__min_samples_leaf\": [1, 5, 10], # minimum samples in a leaf (cutoff)\n",
        "    \"model__max_features\": [\"sqrt\", \"log2\", None] # method of finding the maximum features\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "# pipeline\n",
        "rf_pipe = Pipeline([\n",
        "    (\"model\", RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42))\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# random search\n",
        "rf_search = RandomizedSearchCV(\n",
        "    rf_pipe,\n",
        "    param_distributions=param_dist,\n",
        "    n_iter=25,            # keeps runtime reasonable\n",
        "    scoring=\"roc_auc\",\n",
        "    cv=5,\n",
        "    n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "    random_state=42\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# fitting the model\n",
        "rf_search.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# saving the best model\n",
        "best_rf = rf_search.best_estimator_\n",
        "\n",
        "# best results\n",
        "print(\"Best Params:\", rf_search.best_params_)\n",
        "print(\"Best CV ROC-AUC:\", rf_search.best_score_)"
      ],
