      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**SHAP explainer**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ToEK5nh1VcbL"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Findings***:\n",
        "\n",
        "The tuned Random Forest model achieved the strongest overall predictive performance among the models tested. It demonstrated perfect recall on the test dataset, meaning all approved applicants were correctly identified. Importantly, this high recall did not come at the expense of excessive false positives, as precision and F1 score remained competitive relative to the logistic regression models.\n",
        "\n",
        "Additionally, Random Forest achieved the highest test-set Fβ score, indicating that it best aligned with the chosen evaluation objective emphasizing recall while maintaining reasonable precision. Its ROC-AUC also remained strong, suggesting robust overall ranking ability.\n",
        "\n",
        "Overall, the Random Forest model appears to provide the best balance between capturing qualified applicants and maintaining classification reliability under the selected business-oriented objective."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "aysg4sn_VezA"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Explanation***:\n",
        "\n",
        "Random Forest benefits from ensemble averaging, where predictions from hundreds of decision trees are aggregated. This process reduces model variance and stabilizes predictions compared to a single decision tree.\n",
        "\n",
        "By combining multiple trees trained on bootstrapped samples with feature subsampling, Random Forest:\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Reduces overfitting\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Produces more stable probability estimates\n",
        "\n",
        " - Captures nonlinear relationships\n",
        "\n",
        "These properties likely explain its improved Fβ performance and strong recall without a dramatic loss in precision."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_twSpo4xViMr"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Comparison to Logistic Regression***:\n",
        "\n",
        "Although Random Forest achieved superior predictive performance, logistic regression retains key advantages in interpretability and transparency. Coefficient-based models allow for direct explanation of how individual features influence approval probability, which is particularly important in credit decision contexts where regulatory compliance and fairness considerations matter.\n",
        "\n",
        "Therefore, an optimal strategy may involve:\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Using Random Forest as the primary predictive model for classification performance.\n",
        "\n",
        "  - Using logistic regression as an interpretability benchmark to understand key drivers of approval decisions.\n",
        "\n",
        "This dual-model approach balances predictive strength with transparency and explainability."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "JWslI2KyVqpN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**XGBoost model**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kV-PpHPgVspI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# initialize pipeline\n",
        "xgb_pipe = Pipeline([\n",
        "    (\"model\", XGBClassifier(\n",
        "        random_state=42,\n",
        "        objective=\"binary:logistic\",\n",
        "        eval_metric=\"logloss\",\n",
        "        tree_method=\"hist\"\n",
        "    ))\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "param_dist = {\n",
        "    \"model__n_estimators\": [300, 600, 900, 1200],\n",
        "    \"model__learning_rate\": [0.01, 0.03, 0.05, 0.1],\n",
        "    \"model__max_depth\": [2, 3, 4, 5, 6],\n",
        "    \"model__min_child_weight\": [1, 3, 5, 10],\n",
        "    \"model__subsample\": [0.6, 0.8, 1.0],\n",
        "    \"model__colsample_bytree\": [0.6, 0.8, 1.0],\n",
        "    \"model__gamma\": [0, 0.1, 0.3, 1.0],\n",
        "    \"model__reg_alpha\": [0.0, 0.01, 0.1, 1.0],\n",
        "    \"model__reg_lambda\": [0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 5.0],\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "xgb_search = RandomizedSearchCV(\n",
        "    estimator=xgb_pipe,\n",
        "    param_distributions=param_dist,\n",
        "    n_iter=30,\n",
        "    scoring=\"roc_auc\",\n",
        "    cv=5,\n",
        "    n_jobs=-1,\n",
        "    random_state=42,\n",
        "    verbose=1\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "xgb_search.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "best_xgb = xgb_search.best_estimator_\n",
        "print(\"Best params:\", xgb_search.best_params_)\n",
        "print(\"Best CV ROC-AUC:\", xgb_search.best_score_)"
