        "## SVM Model\n",
        "\n",
        "- Included as an additional classification approach capable of capturing nonlinear decision boundaries through kernel methods.\n",
        "- Particularly useful for moderately sized datasets where linear separability may not hold but complex nonlinear ensemble methods may not be strictly necessary.\n",
        "- Requires feature scaling prior to training, which was addressed using StandardScaler to ensure comparable feature magnitudes.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Reasoning\n",
        "\n",
        "The expected performance improvement of SVM relative to previous models is uncertain. While SVMs are effective when class boundaries are well defined and moderately nonlinear, results from earlier models suggest mixed evidence:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Ensemble nonlinear models such as Random Forest performed strongly, indicating the presence of nonlinear relationships.\n",
        "- However, the single Decision Tree model underperformed, suggesting that nonlinear structure exists but may not be easily captured by a single partitioning approach.\n",
        "- Logistic regression models with regularization also performed well, indicating that a substantial linear signal is present alongside nonlinear effects.\n",
        "\n",
        "Given the moderate dataset size, appropriate feature scaling, and evidence of both linear and nonlinear structure, SVM provides a useful comparative model to evaluate whether margin-based classification offers additional performance gains."
