        "**NOTE:** After controlling for the financial variables, latinos still have a significantly lower approval probability based on the odds ratio they have around a **75% lower chance of approval** which is statistcally significant at the 5% level.\n",
        "\n",
        "However, the dataset is small with **only 57 latino individuals** inside which could lead to unstable estimates and exaggerated coefficients. There are also still many unobserved factors in the dataset like education and the purpose of the loan which could explain this further. yet the difference is very significant to the point that it should be considered when evaluating the bias of this credit card company."
