        "**Conclusion**\n",
        "\n",
        "The industry-level analysis indicates that approval rates vary substantially across employment sectors. However, further examination reveals that much of this variation is explained by underlying financial differences between applicants in different industries.\n",
        "\n",
        "Industries with lower approval rates tend to exhibit higher prior default rates, lower income levels, and weaker credit profiles. When these financial characteristics are accounted for in a regression model, most industry effects disappear.\n",
